No edits. No glitters. No magic.⠀
⠀
This is a bit different from my usual post but this post deserves a place in my Instagram. ⠀
⠀
These are my boys. This is the first time they fasted in the month of Ramadan without their dad (and did wonderfully so) and the first time they are celebrating Eid without their dad. Oh no, this is not a sappy post, I’m just uber proud of them 🥰⠀
⠀
So yesterday, the boys iftar via @zoom_video_communications with their dad and watched  @fauzielaily and @aanurul on Sinar Lebaran - something we do every year, albeit a little different this time. ⠀
⠀
Today, they zoomed with their dad again to wish him Selamat Hari Raya. Trying times, but we have much to be grateful for.⠀
⠀
Eid Mubarak my Muslim friends ❤️
Well done boys for fasting!! Selamat Hari Raya to you & family ❤️ This covid really gives us new experiences ya haha.
Wonderful boys! Sending 💜💜
Happy raya! Your boys really cfm ur factory. All looks alike👍
Selamat Hari Raya my dear! We also did WhatsApp video call this morn with SG family! Virtual greetings but still warmed our hearts

They are so handsome
So cute 😍😍
@ibrightenmyitems I dress them in twinning clothes all the time. Makes it so much easier to decide what to wear and for me to recognise which are my kids when we are out 😂
@thattiredmom Yes! Makes perfect sense! 👌❤️
The biggest praise to you for doing this all alone at the moment!⭐ They are so adorable, and I love their matching shirts! 💙
Awww, Eid Mubarak to you and your family, proud mama ❤️
